Senate Judiciary 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB2459
Gardenhire
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2459 House Bill No. 2206*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 37, Chapter 2, Part 4, is amended by
adding the following new section:
(a) The department of children's services shall not:
(1) Request information regarding the number or type of firearms or
ammunition or identifying information about such firearms or ammunition that a
foster parent or prospective foster parent owns or possesses; or
(2) Request a foster parent or prospective foster parent to display or
provide access to a firearm or ammunition owned or possessed by the parent.
(b) Subsection (a) does not prohibit the department from:
(1) Inquiring whether firearms and ammunition are present in the foster
parent or prospective foster parent's home and, if so, whether such firearms and
ammunition are securely stored; and
(2) Requesting to see the storage of any firearms or ammunition;
provided, that the department shall not request that the foster parent or
prospective foster parent open a secured storage compartment.
(c) This section does not apply to an investigation into an allegation of abuse or
neglect within a foster home.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
